Xpath:---->

	Xpath is a unique locator builder in selenium. Based on html
	tag position xpath target object location....
	
	Xpath available in two types

	1.Absolute xpath           --->index
	2.Relative xpath	     --->attribute
	
	
	
1.Absolute Xpath:--->
	
	Absolute xpath is usefull to target object using tag position. We follow
	absolute when object properties dynamically changing but object position
	 should be static at page...
	 
	 Note:---> In Real time absolute xpath is not prefferable because if client
		change requirement or enhance requirement position automatically change...
	 
Example syntax:--->
		/html/body/div/input[1]

		Nodes in Xpath:--->
				/   ---> RootNode
				// ---> ChildNode
				[ ]  -->  tag index Position
				/  ---> child position to target   [After parent node] 
				
				
Relative Xpath:--->

	
	relative xpath is usefull to target object using attribute names. we use 
	relative xpath when object dynamically changing it's position with in page

				
Syntax for relative xpath:--->

		.//tagname[@propertyname='propertyvalue']

		.---> Current node
	    //--> Current node
		* --> All Elements
		tagname--> Select only related tagelements
		[]--> braces use to target single attribute
		@ --> target only attributes with in innerhtml
		propertyname--> Any unique property
		property-value----?  value w.r.t attribute.
		
==================================================================
Relative xpath categorized into two types.

				1. Xpath Attribute
				2. Xpath text
				
				
HtmlSource:-->

		<div  id="Src_btn" class="Info logo" > Create file </div>	
		
		
		
		Attribute Syntax:-->
					
					//tagname[@propertyname='propertyvalue']
					
					
					By.xpath("//div[@id='Src_btn']")
					
		
		text syntax:-->		
				
				    //tagname[text()='Element text']
					//tagname[.='Element text']
				
				
					By.xpath("//div[text()='Create file']")
					By.xpath("//div[.='Create file']")
					
==========================================================================
				
				
				
				
				
				
	 